WRITE A BRIEF DEFINATION ABOUT GIT AND ITS FEATURES?

GIT IS A OPEN SOURCE SOURCE DISTRIBUTED VERSION CONTROL SYSTEM WHICH IS DESIGNED TO TRACK THE CHANGES IN THE FILES. 
IT CAN ALSO BE USED TO COORDINATE WORK WITH MULTIPLE PEOPLE WHICH CAN SPEED UP THE WORK AND EFFICIENCY.
IT IS USED TO STORE INFORMATION.
IT CAN BE USED PRIVATELY AND PUBLICLY.
IT IS SCALABLE, AS IF THE NUMBER OF USERS INCREASE THEN IT CAN EASILY HANDEL THEM
